frameDefinitions: An Agent disables a flying or floating Patient, causing it to be unable to support itself in its current medium.
In this frame the Patient, an inorganic item, undergoes a chemical process which renders it less useful, desirable or stable. '' '
The Military of a Possessor (either a nation, institution, or private individual) conducts large-scale activities in a Area to accomplish military or combined military/non-military goals.
This frame concerns the decorations that human beings have on or apply to their bodies.
In this frame, the Patient, an inorganic item, undergoes a chemical process caused by another entity, which renders it less useful, desirable or stable.
Under some Condition, usually left implicit, a Responsible_party is required to perform some Duty.
frameExamples: It's rumored that she <t>downed</t> a helicopter with a precisely fired arrow.
